title: Unhandled trie error on geth 1.4.12
body:
A user opened an issue on https://github.com/ethereum/mist/issues/1177 regarding this error message. Any help appreciated :)
#### System information

OS & Version: Windows
#### Expected behaviour

Sync past 2,278,705 block
#### Actual behaviour

`unhandled trie error missing trie node bad block 2,278,705`

I am the user in question
more specifically the error with windows firewall disabled 
E0922 01:05:05.325701 trie/secure_trie.go:74 Unhandled trie error: Missing trie node c677461914a29432e826d405d6f1f4891c72104e61685ae57bcba75d773f75d then a bunch more of those then 
core/blockchaing.go:1126 Bad block #2278705 (0x5f5b302264d1d044247712709e38de0d912157ef38687076affc6e29176690498) 
gas used error (1739942 / 1572760)
 timed out DAO fork-check, dropping
sychronisation failed:block download canceld (requested)

This error usually indicates that the database is corrupted.
There is no fix other than deleting the database and running `geth --fast` to sync again.
Running geth --fast didn't work unless you always have to delete the block chain when you do that idk never have done that before anyway resync from scratch will update tomorrow if it works
@fjl is that block-rewinding command reliable to use in a potentially corrupted database?
No, not in this case unfortunately.
